            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine domini Dei eterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius <rs key="#Emperor/king"
                        >rex</rs></persName>. Omnium fidelium sancte Dei Aeclesie nostrorumque
                        presentium et futurorum comperiat sollicitudo, <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Chaplain">Beatum nostrum <rs key="#Chaplain"
                                >insignem capellanum</rs></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #fidelisOf" ref="#people/188">Grimaldum <rs
                                key="#fidelisOf">nostros dilectos fideles </rs></persName>humiliter
                        nostram adiisse <rs key="#Intercessory">clemenciam</rs>, quatenus pro Dei
                        amore et anime nostre remedio <persName key="#Abbesses" ref="#people/349"
                            >Adlegidam <rs key="#Abbesses">abbatissam</rs></persName><orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbesses">
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">ex cenobio</rs>
                            <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/593"><rs key="#Cities"
                                    >Iustinopolitane civitatis</rs>
                            </placeName></orgName>pariter cum suo monasterio et omnibus rebus
                        substanciisque suis mobilibus et inmobilihus, videlicet <rs key="#Slave"
                            >servis et ancillis,</rs><rs key="#Freeborn"> lib[e]ris</rs> ac <rs
                            key="#Freedman">commendatis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">sub nostre defensionis mundburdum</rs>
                        in integrum recipere dignaremur. Quorum precibus libenter adquiescentes,
                        prefatam Adlegidam abbatissam simul cum suo monasterio et omnibus rebus
                        substanciisque suis mobilibus et inmobilibus, videlicet servis et ancillis,
                        liberis et cartulatis seu et commendatis quicquid dici vel nominari potest
                        sub nostre tuicionis mundburdum suscepimus. simul etiam <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/276"><placeName key="#Curtes"><rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Boundary_disputes">cortem Devisiano</rs></placeName>
                        </geogName>pertinentem de eiusdem monasterio, ex qua <rs
                            key="#Boundary_disputes">altercacio</rs> facta fuit <orgName
                            key="#Bishops"><placeName key="#Cities  #Bishops"
                                >inter Polensem </placeName><rs key="#Bishops"
                            >episcopum</rs></orgName> et eandem abbatissam, nostre defensioni
                        adscribimus, quatenus eandem cortem deinceps prelibate abbatisse habere
                        liceat absque ulla molestia Polensis episcopi. sanccientes quoque iubemus,
                        ut nullus <rs key="#Bishops">(episcopus)</rs>, dux, comes, gastaldius, vel quislibet rei publice exactor prefatam abbatissam
                        aut eius monasterium inquietare vel molestari presumat, seu in eius
                        mansiones potestative ingredi temptet, insuper eius liberi aut cartulati seu
                        et excusati ad publica placita nullatenus ire cogantur, sed liceat
                        prescripte abbatisse deinceps absque alicuius contradiccione sub nostre
                        defensionis vivere mundburdo, remota totius publice potestatis inquietudine.
                        Si quis igitur contra hoc nostre tuicionis umbraculum insurgere aliquando
                        conaverit, sciat se compositurum<rs key="#Penalty"> auri optimi libras
                            .XXX.</rs>, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere palacii nostri
                        </rs>et medietatem prelibate abbatisse vel parti sui monasterii. Quod ut
                        verius credatur et diligencius observetur, anulo nostro assigniri
                        precepimus. Signum (MF) domni Berengarii gloriosissimi regis. <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannes </name><rs
                                key="#Chancellor">cancellarius </rs></persName>ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi <rs
                                key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">episcopi et archicancellarii
                            </rs></persName>recognovi [et] subscripsi (SR) (SI D) Data .VIII. kal.
                        mad., anno dominice incamacionis .DCCCCVIII., domni vero Berengarii piissimi
                        regis .XXI., indictione .XI. Actum<placeName
                            key="#Cities #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/9">
                            <rs key="#Cities #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                >Brixie</rs></placeName>. in Christi nomine feliciter, amen. </ab>
